HocY3K5C0VF-6crd8WFvbbQ ) , streamers =E2=80=94 with the notable exception =
of Prime Video =E2=80=94 have been reluctant to default their audience to a=
n ad-supported tier, giving them scale immediately, which seems inconsisten=
t with their position that their content was good enough to justify their o=
wn streaming business. Netflix, though, has always been customer-first in t=
heir brand promise, long before they had their own content; I don=E2=80=99t=
 think the company could or should move existing subscribers into an ad-sup=
ported tier, but that only makes the challenge of getting scale in their ad=
 business more pressing.

At this point, I think my overall conclusion on this deal is clear: a singl=
e-day NFL package is, unlike most of the other NFL deals, one that is prima=
rily useful for customer acquisition, not churn mitigation. That, meanwhile=
, is exactly what Netflix wants. Moreover, the NFL reaches audiences that N=
etflix wants to reach more effectively than anything else; the challenge/op=
portunity for Netflix will be to retain that audience for the long run, whi=
le monetizing them via ads, which is to say the challenge/opportunity prese=
nted by the NFL is perfectly aligned with Netflix=E2=80=99s corporate objec=
tives.

Netflix Internalizes Ads
------------------------

From Bloomberg ( https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-05-15/netflix=
-says-users-of-subscription-plan-with-ads-hit-40-million ) :

Netflix Inc. said monthly active users of its advertising-supported subscri=
ption plan reached 40 million, and that it will launch an in-house ad techn=
ology platform to support this growing part of its business.

Netflix is working to make ad sales a major new revenue component =E2=80=94=
 and bringing the technology in-house to increase its ability to manage the=
 business. Having its own platform will let the company offer sponsors new =
ways to buy ads as well as measure their effectiveness. In the coming month=
s Netflix will expand its buying capabilities to additional online advertis=
ing companies. The Trade Desk Inc., Google Display & Video 360 and Magnite =
Inc. will join Microsoft Corp. in facilitating automated ad purchases. For =
measurement and verification the company is working with Affinity Solutions=
, DoubleVerify, iSpotTV, Kantar, Nielsen and others.

The ad technology developments follow the company=E2=80=99s announcement ea=
rlier Wednesday that it will air two National Football League games on Chri=
stmas Day as part of a three-season deal.

