Comcast=E2=80=99s Bundle
----------------

From Variety ( https://variety.com/2024/tv/news/peacock-netflix-apple-tv-pl=
us-bundle-streaming-comcast-1236002375/ ) :

Get ready for the next cable-like streaming bundle: Comcast later this mont=
h will launch a three-way bundle =E2=80=94 with Peacock, Netflix and Apple =
TV+ =E2=80=94 offered at a deep discount, Comcast chief Brian Roberts said.=
 Dubbed StreamSaver, the bundle will be available to all Comcast broadband =
and TV customers, Roberts said, speaking Tuesday at MoffettNathanson=E2=80=
=99s 2024 Media, Internet and Communications Conference in New York.

The three streaming services, Peacock, Netflix and Apple TV+, will =E2=80=
=9Ccome at a vastly reduced price to anything in the market today,=E2=80=9D=
 Roberts said, although he didn=E2=80=99t reveal any pricing details. =E2=
=80=9CAnd that=E2=80=99s an everyday pricing, not an introductory pricing.=
=E2=80=9D The goal is to =E2=80=9Cadd value to consumers=E2=80=9D and at th=
e same time =E2=80=9Ctake some of the dollars out of=E2=80=9D other compani=
es=E2=80=99 streaming businesses, Roberts added, while reinforcing Comcast=
=E2=80=99s broadband service offerings. =E2=80=9CWe=E2=80=99ve been bundlin=
g video successfully and creatively for 60 years, and so this is the latest=
 iteration of that,=E2=80=9D Roberts said. =E2=80=9CI think this will be a =
pretty compelling package.=E2=80=9D

The cheapest way to get all three streamers separately today is with the ad=
-supported Peacock Premium ($5.99/month, going up to $7.99/month in July); =
Netflix Basic with ads, which costs $6.99/month; and the standard Apple TV+=
 plan at $9.99/month. Note that to get Comcast=E2=80=99s StreamSaver discou=
nt, you will need to already subscribe to Xfinity Internet and/or Xfinity T=
V.

This isn=E2=80=99t the only new bundle coming: Disney and Warner Bros. Disc=
overy announced plans for their own streaming bundle ( https://variety.com/=
2024/digital/news/disney-plus-hulu-max-bundle-1235996533/ ) as well. The po=
int of all of them is exactly what I have been harping about for years: the=
 most important part of a sustainable subscription business is reducing chu=
rn, and it=E2=80=99s a lot easier to reduce churn when you are not solely r=
esponsible for keeping consumers happy, but can instead share the load.

What is notable about this Comcast offering is that it includes Netflix. Th=
is could mean two things. First, to the extent that Netflix is a part of th=
is deal, I suspect they are giving up the smallest amount of revenue, given=
 that their churn mitigation is already excellent. That doesn=E2=80=99t mea=
n they won=E2=80=99t give up anything, though: Netflix has long sold itself=
 via the cable companies, which remain effective at reaching audiences that=
 aren=E2=80=99t traditional streaming customers.

Second, it=E2=80=99s plausible that Netflix isn=E2=80=99t giving up anythin=
g at all: Comcast appears to be unilaterally offering this deal solely to i=
ts broadband and cable customers; it has margin to play with in terms of th=
e former in particular. That, though, raises the eternal question of what e=
xactly is the point of Peacock, other than spending Comcast=E2=80=99s broad=
